## 2. System Architecture

| Component          | Role                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **PC 1 (Server)**  | - Paired to the Bluetooth mouse (HID profile).  <br> - Captures raw HID events (mouse/keyboard) via OS API. <br> - Detects the five‐click toggle. <br> - Serializes and sends each event over Bluetooth to PC 2. <br> - Manages state: LOCAL\_CONTROL ↔ FORWARDING ↔ DISCONNECTED. |
| **PC 2 (Client)**  | - Paired to PC 1 (SPP or BLE GATT). <br> - Performs initial handshake (HELLO/ACK). <br> - Receives serialized events, drops duplicates via sequence/source tags. <br> - Injects events into local OS input. <br> - Sends heartbeats; handles reconnects and state sync.            |
| **Bluetooth Link** | - Wireless channel carrying control messages and input‐event payloads. <br> - Could be Bluetooth Classic SPP (no fragmentation, higher throughput) or BLE (20 B MTU, low power).                                                                                                   |

