## 12. Operating-System-Specific Injection & Capture

| OS      | Capture API                             | Injection API                                 | Notes                                                                    |
| ------- | --------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Windows | RegisterRawInputDevices & WM\_INPUT     | SendInput (MOUSEINPUT / KEYBDINPUT structs)   | No driver install needed; requires window message pump or message hook.  |
| Linux   | `/dev/input/eventX` (evdev) in non-grab | `/dev/uinput` (create virtual device + write) | Application must run as root or have `CAP_SYS_ADMIN` to open uinput.     |
| macOS   | IOHIDManager (no seize)                 | CGEventCreateMouseEvent / CGEventPost         | App must be signed with “HID” entitlements for injection in newer macOS. |

* **Windows Raw Input Example:**

  * Pros: easily target a specific HID by Vendor ID / Product ID; no root needed.
  * Cons: you must have a window message pump and your app window must remain open (could be hidden).
* **Linux evdev + uinput Example:**

  * Pros: precise, low latency.
  * Cons: requires elevated privileges; user must allow uinput.
* **macOS IOHIDManager + CGEvent Example:**

  * Pros: full HID power.
  * Cons: newer macOS versions require explicit permissions to “monitor input” and to “simulate input”; user must grant Accessibility permission.

